                ".In the higher energy range (E(n) about 150 to 600 keV)",
                " the measurements is based on the (n,p) scattering",
                " cross section.",
                ".In order to join the two parts of the cross section",
                " curve a number of angular distributions was measured,",
                " and a comparison was made with the corresponding",
                " measurements of Austin (private communication) at",
                " equal proton energies but only for those laboratory",
                " angles where the neutrons are emitted with energies",
                " above 80 keV."
              ]
            }
